I'm going to talk about Highlands Coffee, which is a Vietnamese coffee shop chain and distributor of coffee products.
My favorite branch is located within a walking distance from where I live. If I'm not mistaken, I first step inside this building when I was a fresher at university. At that time, it was on the weekend, so I and my closed friends decided to take a little retreat and he suggested this coffee chain. And since then, I have become a regular (loyal customer) and paid it a visit again and again.
On the outside, it has a facade made from crystal clear glass, which provides customers with a lively and bustling view of people and vehicles rushing back and forth on the nearby road. In constract to vibrant surroundings, the inside is kept quiet and spotlessly clean while the smell of high-quality coffee lingers in the air. They also play soft and gentle music in the background. This combination creates a homey vibe for anyone crave a cup of coffee.
Highlands Coffee boasts an extensive menu of speciality coffees at a reasonable price. The signature drinks area handcrafted beverages made from Vietnamese coffee beans. There is also a variety of teas and iced blended drinks if you can't stand the bitterness of coffee. Moreover, I do not come here only for the view or the beverages but also for the excellent customer service. The staff is well-trained and cater to the guests' needs quite well.
I often come here to study because of its quality ambience. I can make most of my studies while the coffee keeps me awake.
 If you're looking for a great coffee place to go to, I high recommend Highlands Coffee.

